column5: Thats awesome! thanks for sharing that!

The Chinook run in the Ganny is larger then the spring steelhead run, in some years almost double the number of fish, and it was last stocked with chinooks in 1969, so it looks like a combination of natural reproduction, and stupid fish who dont know how to imprint on the rivers where they were born
awesome. they are all waiting for a heavy rainfall to move up the river.
I stopped by today, some nice brown trout mixed in with the chinooks waiting to move upstream.
Its quite spectacular really, the fish migration upstream... cool video
